body:
Can you run the following script on your system and report the results, i.e. install Go and run `go run test.go`

```golang
package main

import (
	"fmt"
	"path/filepath"
)

func main() {
	fmt.Println(filepath.EvalSymlinks("/home/piotr/storage/synced/oneplus5/"))
}
```

In any case we need to act on, not just ignore an error when determining the root with symlinks evaluated: https://github.com/syncthing/syncthing/blob/master/lib/fs/basicfs.go#L56  
Either panic already there (probably a bad idea, though I don't get why it should ever fail), or disable watching to prevent panics.

@jamiesonbecker Yes, that hash is correct.  

Maybe you need to login somehow to teamcity before the link can be accessed.

And yes, I'd be interested in the panic trace. The trace shouldn't contain any personal information, but you can email it to me if you like. It might be related, but in that case it was a "folder already running" panic, not a nil deref.
